  "text": "We're ready now to show how the Virasoro Ward identity arises from the subleading soft theorem. Let A n+1 ({p i } i∈{1,...,n} , q) be the n + 1 scattering amplitude involving n massless particles and one graviton of momentum q µ and polarization ǫ (±) µν (q). The soft limit for the graviton of momentum q → 0 gives [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] A n+1 ({p i } i∈{1,...,n} , q) → S is the sum of the spin and angular momentum of the j-th particle. Let's focus, without loss of generality, on the minus helicity case. In the coordinates (ω, z,z) the subleading soft factor becomes",
